            <li class="nv-talk"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia_talk:WikiProject_Trains/nav" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia talk:WikiProject Trains/nav"><span title="Discuss this template">talk</span></a></li>
            <li class="nv-edit"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/nav&amp;action=edit"><span title="Edit this template">edit</span></a></li>
           </ul>
          </div> </th>
        </tr>
       </tbody>
      </table> 
      <p>Welcome to <b>WikiProject Trains</b> on the English Wikipedia! We are a <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject">group</a> of editors who aim to streamline and co-ordinate the expansion of train-related articles. If you would like to join the project, simply <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Members&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1">add your name</a> to the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Members" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Members">list of participants</a>. Please browse our resources at your leisure; we hope you find them useful. </p> 
      <hr> 
      <p><b><a href="/wiki/Special:RecentChangesLinked/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Recent_changes" title="Special:RecentChangesLinked/Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Recent changes">Recent changes in rail transport-related articles</a></b> (<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Recent_changes" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Recent changes">list</a>) </p> 
      <hr> 
      <dl>
       <dt>
        Goals
       </dt> 
       <dd> 
        <ul>
         <li>To create the foremost <a href="/wiki/Reliability_of_Wikipedia" title="Reliability of Wikipedia">reliable and accurate</a> free-content encyclopedia of trains in the English language.</li> 
         <li>To improve coverage of trains by creating, expanding, and maintaining articles that describe all of its aspects.</li> 
         <li>To provide guidelines and recommendations for such articles, and to serve as the central point of discussion for issues related to trains in Wikipedia.</li>
        </ul>
       </dd>
      </dl> 
      <dl>
       <dt>
        Scope
       </dt> 
       <dd>
        The project generally considers <i>any</i> article related to historical or contemporary train-related affairs to be within its scope. A more detailed description of the scope, and our primary areas of focus within it, may be found in the <a href="#Scope">section on project scope</a>.
       </dd>
      </dl> 
      <dl>
       <dt>
        Structure
       </dt> 
       <dd>
        The project aims solely to assist the authoring of reliable and accurate trains articles in accordance with our Goals [above]. Internally, the project had developed several structural features to assist in the management of our workload: 
        <ul>
         <li><a href="#Task_forces">Task forces</a>: informal groups for collaboration on specific train-related topics.</li> 
         <li><a href="#Departments">Departments</a>: areas of the project which streamline work—such as article review and outside opinions—that "supports" the main body of article writers.</li>
        </ul>
       </dd>
      </dl> 
      <p>General discussion relating to this project takes place on <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia_talk:WikiProject_Trains" title="Wikipedia talk:WikiProject Trains">Wikipedia talk:WikiProject Trains</a>; suggestions or comments are welcome there. </p>

      <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Scope"><span class="anchor" id="SCOPE"></span>Scope</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Scope">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> 
      <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1007196855">
      <div class="module-shortcutanchordiv">
       <span id="WP:RR#SCOPE"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="module-shortcutboxplain plainlist noprint" role="note">
       <div class="module-shortcutlist">
        <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Shortcut" title="Wikipedia:Shortcut">Shortcut</a>
       </div>
       <ul>
        <li><span class="plainlinks"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:RR&amp;redirect=no#SCOPE">WP:RR#SCOPE</a></span></li>
       </ul>
      </div> 
      <p>The project is concerned primarily with train and railroad/railway subjects, and considers any article relating to those topics to be within its scope. </p>
      <p>By extension, the scope of the project includes—but is not limited to—the following: </p> 
      <ol>
       <li>Train—including passenger, metro, light rail, goods, and locomotive—units.</li> 
       <li>Railroad engineering and technology.</li> 
       <li>Railway stations and halts.</li> 
       <li>Railway routes and lines.</li> 
       <li>Railroad operators.</li> 
       <li>Manufacturers of train units and of railroad apparatus.</li> 
       <li>Organisations whose main business is with railroads.</li>
      </ol> 
      <style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r936637989">.mw-parser-output .portal{border:solid #aaa 1px;padding:0}.mw-parser-output .portal.tleft{margin:0.5em 1em 0.5em 0}.mw-parser-output .portal.tright{margin:0.5em 0 0.5em 1em}.mw-parser-output .portal>ul{display:table;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0.1em;max-width:175px;background:#f9f9f9;font-size:85%;line-height:110%;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold}.mw-parser-output .portal>ul>li{display:table-row}.mw-parser-output .portal>ul>li>span:first-child{display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center}.mw-parser-output .portal>ul>li>span:last-child{display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle}</style>
      <div role="navigation" aria-label="Portals" class="noprint portal plainlist tright"> 
       <ul> 
        <li><span><a href="/wiki/File:P_train.svg" class="image"><img alt="icon" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e3/P_train.svg/31px-P_train.svg.png" decoding="async" width="31" height="28" class="noviewer" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e3/P_train.svg/47px-P_train.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e3/P_train.svg/62px-P_train.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="400" data-file-height="360"></a></span><span><a href="/wiki/Portal:Trains" title="Portal:Trains">Trains portal</a></span></li>
       </ul>
      </div> 
      <p>Highlights of this project's output are listed on <b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Trains" title="Portal:Trains">Portal:Trains</a></b> </p>

      <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Members">Members</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Members">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> 
      <p>The current list of project participants is quite large and is located on the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Members" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Members">/Members</a> page. You may add yourself to this list if you want. </p> 
      <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Task_forces"><span class="anchor" id="TF"></span>Task forces</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Task forces">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> 
      <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1007196855">
      <div class="module-shortcutanchordiv">
       <span id="WP:RR#TF"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="module-shortcutboxplain plainlist noprint" role="note">
       <div class="module-shortcutlist">
        <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Shortcut" title="Wikipedia:Shortcut">Shortcut</a>
       </div>
       <ul>
        <li><span class="plainlinks"><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:RR&amp;redirect=no#TF">WP:RR#TF</a></span></li>
       </ul>
      </div> 
      <p>Task forces are informal collaboration groups of WikiProject Trains members focusing on certain subtopics of rail transport. The current task forces—and their respective focus and remit—include: </p> 
      <table class="wikitable"> 
       <tbody>
        <tr> 
         <th>Task Force </th> 
         <th>Scope and focus </th>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Article_maintenance_task_force" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Article maintenance task force">Article maintenance task force</a> </td> 
         <td>Performing mundane tasks such as bypassing disambigs and monitoring the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Todo/Write" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Todo/Write">list of articles to write</a>. </td>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Assessment_request_backlog_elimination_drive" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Assessment request backlog elimination drive">Assessment request backlog elimination drive</a> </td> 
         <td>To assess articles which are requested. </td>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/By_country_series_task_force" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/By country series task force">By country series task force</a> </td> 
         <td>Articles in the <a href="/wiki/Rail_transport_by_country" title="Rail transport by country">Rail transport by country</a> and <a href="/wiki/History_of_rail_transport_by_country" class="mw-redirect" title="History of rail transport by country">History of rail transport by country</a> series. </td>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Categories_task_force" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Categories task force">Categories task force</a> </td> 
         <td>Standardize the categories under <a href="/wiki/Category:Rail_transport" title="Category:Rail transport">Category:Rail transport</a> into a comprehensive system of categories. </td>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Images_task_force" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Images task force">Images task force</a> </td> 
         <td>Create and locate suitable images for use on rail transport articles and replace fair use images with free images where available and appropriate. </td>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Locomotives_task_force" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Locomotives task force">Locomotives task force</a> </td> 
         <td>Articles about <a href="/wiki/Locomotive" title="Locomotive">locomotives</a> throughout history, worldwide. </td>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Maps_task_force" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Maps task force">Maps task force</a> </td> 
         <td>Create and maintain standardized maps of railroad routes for rail transport articles. </td>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Operations_task_force" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Operations task force">Operations task force</a> </td> 
         <td>Articles about rail transport operations with particular attention to organization and inter-system generalization. </td>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Passenger_trains_task_force" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Passenger trains task force">Passenger trains task force</a> </td> 
         <td>Articles about passenger trains and passenger train equipment. </td>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Portal_task_force" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Portal task force">Portal task force</a> </td> 
         <td>Maintenance and content updates of <a href="/wiki/Portal:Trains" title="Portal:Trains">Portal:Trains</a>. </td>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Rail_transport_modelling_task_force" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Rail transport modelling task force">Rail transport modelling task force</a> </td> 
         <td>Articles related to <a href="/wiki/Rail_transport_modelling" title="Rail transport modelling">rail transport modelling</a>. </td>
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Timelines_task_force" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Timelines task force">Timelines task force</a> </td> 
         <td>Articles in <a href="/wiki/Category:Rail_transport_timelines" title="Category:Rail transport timelines">Category:Rail transport timelines</a> and the "Selected anniversaries" and "Trains news" sections of <a href="/wiki/Portal:Trains" title="Portal:Trains">Portal:Trains</a> </td>
        </tr>
       </tbody>
      </table> 
      <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Coordination">Coordination</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Coordination">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> 
      <p>The coordination of the project is undertaken in accordance with <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Strategy" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Strategy">Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Strategy</a>. </p> 
      <ul>
       <li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Article_templates" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Article templates">/Article templates</a> - templates that can be used on rail transport articles.</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Assessment" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Assessment">/Assessment</a> - Rating rail transport articles based on a standard Wikipedia-wide scale as part of the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Version_1.0_Editorial_Team" title="Wikipedia:Version 1.0 Editorial Team">Version 1.0</a> efforts.</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Peer_review" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Peer review">/Peer review</a> - Reviewing articles by project members; such a review could be part of the path toward <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WIAFA" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:WIAFA">Featured article</a> status.</li>
      </ul> 
      <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Resources">Resources</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Resources">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> 
      <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Editing">Editing</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Editing">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> 
      <ul>
       <li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Todo" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Todo">Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Todo</a>: articles identified as needing attention and improvement.</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Pages_needing_attention/Railroads" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:Pages needing attention/Railroads">Wikipedia:Pages needing attention/Railroads</a>.</li>

      </ul>

      <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Showcase">Showcase</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Showcase">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> 
      <p>The following is a listing of articles (and other types of content) within <a href="#Scope">the scope of the project</a> that have been noted and recognized for their outstanding quality. Project members may peruse these at their leisure: they all serve as excellent examples of different writing and organizational styles that one may wish to emulate. </p> 
      <table class="plainlinks ombox ombox-notice" role="presentation">
       <tbody>
        <tr>
         <td class="mbox-image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1d/Information_icon4.svg/40px-Information_icon4.svg.png" decoding="async" width="40" height="40" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1d/Information_icon4.svg/60px-Information_icon4.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1d/Information_icon4.svg/80px-Information_icon4.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="620" data-file-height="620"></td>
         <td class="mbox-text">This is a list of recognized content, updated weekly by <a href="/wiki/User:JL-Bot" title="User:JL-Bot">JL-Bot</a>&nbsp;(<a href="/wiki/User_talk:JL-Bot" title="User talk:JL-Bot">talk</a>&nbsp;<b>·</b> <a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/JL-Bot" title="Special:Contributions/JL-Bot">contribs</a>). There is no need to edit the list yourself. If an article is missing from the list, make sure it is <a href="/wiki/User:JL-Bot/Project_content#Project_parameter" title="User:JL-Bot/Project content">tagged</a> (e.g. {{<a href="/wiki/Template:WikiProject_Trains" title="Template:WikiProject Trains">WikiProject Trains</a>}}) or <a href="/wiki/User:JL-Bot/Project_content#Project_parameter" title="User:JL-Bot/Project content">categorized</a> correctly. See <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:RECOG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:RECOG">WP:RECOG</a> for configuration options.</td>
        </tr>
       </tbody>
      </table>

        <li><a href="/wiki/Rail_transport_in_Walt_Disney_Parks_and_Resorts" title="Rail transport in Walt Disney Parks and Resorts">Rail transport in Walt Disney Parks and Resorts</a> <small>(2017-07-17)</small></li> 
        <li><a href="/wiki/List_of_Nanjing_Metro_stations" title="List of Nanjing Metro stations">List of Nanjing Metro stations</a> <small>(2017-09-01)</small></li> 
        <li><a href="/wiki/List_of_Metro_(Minnesota)_light_rail_stations" title="List of Metro (Minnesota) light rail stations">List of Metro (Minnesota) light rail stations</a> <small>(2018-06-25)</small></li> 
        <li><a href="/wiki/London_station_group" title="London station group">London station group</a> <small>(2018-07-16)</small></li>
       </ul>

      <h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Former_featured_articles_2">Former featured articles</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Former featured articles">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3> 
      <div style="margin: 0.5em;">
       <div class="floatright">
        <a href="/wiki/File:Featured_article_star_-_cross.svg" class="image"><img alt="Featured article star - cross.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/Featured_article_star_-_cross.svg/50px-Featured_article_star_-_cross.svg.png" decoding="async" width="50" height="50" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/Featured_article_star_-_cross.svg/75px-Featured_article_star_-_cross.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/Featured_article_star_-_cross.svg/100px-Featured_article_star_-_cross.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="180" data-file-height="180"></a>
       </div>
      </div> 
      <p>These articles were at one time <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Featured_articles" title="Wikipedia:Featured articles">Featured</a> but <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Former_featured_articles" title="Wikipedia:Former featured articles">no longer are</a>. The rationale behind removing Featured status from these articles will be given or linked to on the article's respective talk page. Project members may wish to use this list to identify articles that may require less workload in order to pull up to Featured status and which have a ready-made (by means of the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:FAC" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:FAC">Featured article candidate</a> discussion and of the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:FAR" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:FAR">Featured article review</a> discussion respectively) source of feedback on possible strengths and possible weaknesses. </p>
      <p>In alphabetical order: </p> 
      <ul>
       <li><a href="/wiki/2007_Samjhauta_Express_bombings" title="2007 Samjhauta Express bombings">2007 Samjhauta Express bombings</a> - listed 24, 2008 delisted February 3, 2011</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/BC_Rail" title="BC Rail">BC Rail</a> - front page feature October 4, 2005 delisted June 2009</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/C%C4%83ile_Ferate_Rom%C3%A2ne" title="C?ile Ferate Române">C?ile Ferate Române</a> - front page feature July 22, 2005 delisted May 24, 2009</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/Canadian_Pacific_Railway" title="Canadian Pacific Railway">Canadian Pacific Railway</a> - front page feature April 23, 2005 delisted May 2009</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/Franklin_B._Gowen" title="Franklin B. Gowen">Franklin B. Gowen</a> (president of the <a href="/wiki/Reading_Railroad" class="mw-redirect" title="Reading Railroad">Reading Railroad</a>) - listed March 15, 2005 delisted September 1, 2009</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/Indian_Railways" title="Indian Railways">Indian Railways</a> - front page feature October 16, 2005 delisted January 24, 2009</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/Isambard_Kingdom_Brunel" title="Isambard Kingdom Brunel">Isambard Kingdom Brunel</a> - front page feature March 23, 2006 delisted November 12, 2009.</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/London_Underground" title="London Underground">London Underground</a> - main page feature, June 21, 2004 delisted December 29, 2006</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/Rail_transport_in_India" title="Rail transport in India">Rail transport in India</a> - front page feature August 16, 2007 delisted August 3, 2009</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/SkyTrain_(Vancouver)" title="SkyTrain (Vancouver)">SkyTrain (Vancouver)</a> - listed June 19, 2007 delisted June 30, 2010</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/TGV" title="TGV">TGV</a> - main page feature, January 15, 2006; delisted on May 9, 2008.</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/Wigwag_(railroad)" title="Wigwag (railroad)">Wigwag (railroad)</a> - main page feature, July 5, 2004; delisted on March 26, 2007.</li> 
       <li><a href="/wiki/William_N._Page" class="mw-redirect" title="William N. Page">William N. Page</a> (co founder of the <a href="/wiki/Virginian_Railway" title="Virginian Railway">Virginian Railway</a>) - listed November 18, 2004 delisted November 11, 2008</li>
      </ul>

      <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Article_alerts"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains/Article_alerts" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Trains/Article alerts">Article alerts</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:WikiProject_Trains&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Article alerts">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2> 
      <p><span class="anchor" id="AAstart"></span> <span class="anchor" id="DYKN"></span><span style="font-weight: bold">Did you know</span> </p>

                </ul>

            <ul>
             <li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Council" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Council">WikiProject Council</a>
